  "prompt": "What are alternate sayings to \"two peas in a pod\"?",
  "response": "Certainly! Here are some alternative expressions to \"two peas in a pod\":\n\n1. Birds of a feather\n2. Cut from the same cloth\n3. Like two drops of water\n4. Thick as thieves\n5. As alike as two pins\n6. Matches made in heaven\n7. Tweedledum and Tweedledee\n8. Similar as twins\n9. Just like old friends\n10. The same in every way\n\nThese phrases convey the idea of two people who are very similar or who share a close bond.",
